title: When it works, it‚Äôs great but....
reviewText: This is the glitchiest app I use and it's frustrating that a mammoth of a financial institution cannot invest in a more robust mobile application. Almost every time I try to use mobile deposit, it hangs up. Usually this happens during the photo step. Often though, I get all the way to the end and try to finish the deposit and I get a pop up message that it failed and to try again later. Sometimes it fails all day and I have to wait until a day or two later. I turn off my phone and try refreshing it that way. I look for updates. Nothing will correct it.  So I'm sitting on checks that I can't deposit unless I go to a branch and that sort of defeats the purpose of a mobile app. Admittedly, I've considered switching banks because it's happening more often now than it did a year or two ago, but I don't have time to read reviews to see if any other banks have better technology. This is among the most frustrating apps I have. I get anxiety every time I need to deposit because I almost can predict that it's going to take me all day to try dozens of attempts. It's like I have to set aside a good time to go to work at it. My brother and daughter use the same bank/app and we recently shared our frustrations so I know it's not my phone. (Sigh)

title: Unhappy
reviewText: I started with Bank of America in 1986 then called  Annette Bank.  Used only the checking and only paid bills.  Not to long ago someone hacked my account and ordered an atm card unknown too me and begin too use it @ 3 or so in the morning.  The alert went off,  I called the bank, they said it would be cut off,  however when my wife and I went to the bank and we were there when it opened they were still going from place to place withdrawing monies as well as making charges while we were sitting in front of the banking representative.   My problem was and is since they didn't give me my monies back,  although I did everything I was told to do and then some.  I asked look at my history and see how this fits me.1). I made 2 separate police reports 2) I've never requested or had gotten an atm card in 34 years3) I called on the first alert to stop charges @3am4) I've never used an atm especially to withdraw funds5) I've never used an atm card to purchase items for at shoe stores or any other place.6) I asked to use the pictures taken of who was at the atm,  there reply was it could've been a family member.7) police told me that people order the cards after gaining info and check your mailbox daily they said it happens all the time.8) hence I've now gotten a mailbox that requires a key!9) what gets us is we were in the branch and the people were still allowed too use the card after it was supposedly cut off.Unbelievable Needless to say I've changed banks and requested anyone I know to do the same,  I loved Bank of America until as a working man I feel they didn't put effort into resolving this situation and left me holding the bag. reviewText: In the old iPad version of the app, your checking account information opened in a large, easy to read window that made use of the iPad's wide screen. In the new app, your checking account information is shoehorned into a small narrow strip the the left of the screen, while the right side is cluttered with large boxes that take up space, for things that I don't really need very often. Who at Bank of America thought this was good, user friendly design? It's a joke! It's a very poor design, and a very poor use of the extra space provided by the iPad. Not to mention the poor choice of coloring the amounts blue, instead of black (like it used to be), over a white background, which just makes it that much more difficult to read. There's an old saying, "If it ain't broke, don't fix it."

reviewText: The bill-pay system is designed to encourage you to become overdrawn accidentally. When you ask to see all of the bill payments scheduled, it does NOT show the bill payments scheduled by the other.  So each of carries on thinking you have the whole story, when in fact you don't. The complaints feature of the app doesn't work properly, so the only way I have found to report this is via a review.

title: New Version is AWFUL!!!!
reviewText: I rarely bother writing reviews on apps, because, frankly, I'm too busy with other things...but BoA has taken a useful, if somewhat limited mobile app, (which, let me add, I loved, because while it didn't do everything I needed‚ÄîI could modify or setup a single payment on it!), and filled it with info I didn't want or ask for (one third of the screen in landscape position on my iPad Pro is now given over to non-essential items), but it's apparently lost the ONE functionality I wanted:  modifying or making payments.Mind you...I steadfastly ignored all requests to update the app until they forced me to do so, this am, due to the high number of complaints about it...but I did so, feeling that given the long ramp up time, this would allow the developers to at least work out the OBVIOUS bugs, even if I was left with the oft-complained about by others, feature bloat.But nope.  Here I am...logging in...no longer able to see a comfortable, wide view of JUST my account information...and the one payment I needed to modify...would not allow it.Oh, it let me move from field to field...and took my new value...but of the two buttons at the bottom of the field, "Cancel" and "Modify"‚Äîonly "Cancel" worked.  Hitting "Modify"‚Äîregardless of what changes I made‚Äîdid nothing.  NADA.  Zip.QA‚Äîwhat the heck are you doing????  (I work for a software company as a Product Manager‚Äîwhere I work very closely with Dev and QA every day, and this is the sort of egregious oversight that makes me scratch my head:  modifying an existing payment is NOT an edge case‚Äîit's a typical use case!!!)REALLY unhappy.  Please...get rid of the overhead of all the bells and whistles‚Äîand focus on core product functionality:  checking account balances and setting up and modifying payments.  There's really nothing else I want from a banking app!!!!
